#Using PCA_Segmentation with pipenv
# 1.
#-Check the version of torch used in the project,
#-Check the available wheels of a cuda version available for that version of torch
#--url for wheels of torch: https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu117/ (for cuda 11.7)
#--currently the torch version ==2.0.0, which has an available version for my target system (windows) shown at the url
#-If you have Cuda installed, check your version using command "nvidia-smi",
#--else install a cuda version compatible with the torch wheel you want to use from the nvidia website
#-Check if it was installed correctly with trhe command "nvcc --version" in command prompt
#In the current case of torch 2.0.0 and cuda 11.7, run the following command in the terminal to install torch with cuda support:
#pipenv install --index https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu117/ "torch==2.0.0+cu117"
# 2.
# To get scipy to install, make sure to install Cython first by itself.
# To get numpy to install use 'pipenv run pip install --no-use-pep517 numpy'
# To get h5py to install use 'pipenv in'

